{"word":"H8551 - תָּמַךְ - tâmak - taw-mak' - Hold","slug":"H8551","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">תָּמַךְ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tâmak"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>taw-mak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Hold"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05DE;&#x05DA; - ta&#x0302;mak</b> - <i>taw-mak'</i><p/>A primitive root; to sustain; by implication to <i>obtain</i>, <i>keep fast</i>; figuratively to <i>help</i>, <i>follow close: - </i>(take, up-) hold (up), maintain, retain, stay (up)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8543\">H8543</a>, <a href=\"#/H865\">H865</a>"}]}